OL,4,Cdeath of father and son by dangerous
OL,5,Cdriving
OL,7,FA solicitor for Mr Petrov said that
OL,8,Fthe defendant cannot remember the
OL,9,Factual accident or the collision and
OL,10,Fthat his last memory was feeling that
OL,11,Fhis blood sugar was low, to which the
OL,12,Fconstable agreed.
OL,14,FAn application for bail was made and
OL,15,Fthe court heard Mr Petrov's mother had
OL,16,Fprovided her son's passport and
OL,17,Foffered surety.
OL,19,FThe court heard that police believe he
OL,20,Fis a "serious" flight risk and
OL,21,Fobjected to bail.
